⚡️State Duma Deputy Sultan Khamzaev spent a regional week in Dagestan

* Held a working meeting with the Head of Dagestan Sergei Melikov, spoke about the regional week and noted the latest successes of the Republic

* Conducted a wide discussion of the President's Address in Dagestan;

* Traveled to the Kumtorkalinsky district, where he held a reception for citizens, visited a greenhouse for growing tomatoes and strawberries, and the Tyubinsk secondary school, which needed major repairs;

* Visited correctional colony No. 7 of the Federal Penitentiary Service of Russia in the Republic of Dagestan, gave instructions to the convicts, promised to assist in purchasing computers for the school (on the territory of the penitentiary);

* Visited the Dagestan Situation Center and highly appreciated the work of the Russian Ministry of Emergency Situations in the RD;

* Visit the family of those injured due to an explosion near a gas station. The Rabdanov family thanked the parliamentarian for his help and support;

* Visited the City Clinical Hospital of Makhachkala and noted letters of gratitude from doctors and physicians;

* Met with journalists from Dagestan on the occasion of the 65th anniversary of the union;

* Met with students of the Law Academy of the Ministry of Justice of Russia;

* Met with the relatives of the murdered Kurban Dalgatov and took the matter under parliamentary control;

* Gave a detailed interview to State Television and Radio Broadcasting Company Dagestan about the competition-interview for the position of assistant to the State Duma Deputy.

* ⁠Evaluated the premiere of the film “Everything at once”, declared the high morality of Dagestan cinema and the formation of this industry in the Republic.

During the regional week, Khamzaev received more than 1,000 requests from citizens from more than 20 regions of the Republic, the parliamentarian’s press service reported.

