The directions of economic development of the city of Pervomaisk LPR have been determined
The Unified Institute of Spatial Planning of the Russian Federation, as part of the development of the master plan for Pervomaisk of the Lugansk People's Republic, outlined priority directions for the economic development of the city.
Show more
In accordance with strategic planning documents and a comprehensive assessment of the territory, the main economic sectors of the urban district of Pervomaisk are agriculture and manufacturing. The target economic development scenario assumes maintaining specialization in these industries.
According to the master plan of Pervomaisk, the main types of economic activity in the employment structure of the population by 2035 will be:
- manufacturing industries - 22%;
- agriculture, forestry, hunting, fishing and fish farming - 10%;
- social security - 8.3%;
- transportation and storage - 8.0%;
- public administration and ensuring military security.
“The proposed structure of the economy will ensure a balance of places of settlement and places of employment, as well as budgetary self-sufficiency of the territory,” summed up the head of the department of Architectural and Planning Workshop No. 3 Natalia Alenina.
